1. Have a bibliography
  - Data sets (url, link to the github)
  - Packages used

2. Label figures and tables
  - include a caption if possible!

3. Include tables for all results
  - Did you do a regression? Include the results!
  - (Show the most amount of data in least amount of words; the more simple the better; make it easy for the reader)

4. Show don't tell
  - Visuals are more compelling than lines of text

5. Microsoft Word is a joke
  - There's something unprofessional about the appearance of .docx
  - You'll really impress people with well formatted .pdfs generated by more advanced type setting tools
    - .qmd?
    - .md?
    - LaTeX?
